    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I should not have wrote so soon but for my flutter on <choice>
                        <abbr>acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                        </abbr>
                        <expan>account</expan>
                    </choice>
                    of the american news. you perhaps will <sic>so</sic> good as to fling some light on it. I attribute it to th<gap unit="chars" quantity="1" reason="illegible"/>
                    <supplied>e</supplied>
                    precipitate motions of <persName ref="pe0472">
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>G.</abbr>
                            <expan>General</expan>
                        </choice> Conway</persName>;
                    <note type="editorial">Henry Seymour Conway, referred to by contemporaries as General Conway (1719–1795), showed outright opposition to the war against the American colonies from its beginning, presented motions in favour of peace on 27 February 1782, and argued in November 1782 that the provisional articles made with America should make independence unconditional. ODNB; Correspondence of Horace Walpole with George Montague, Esq. [and others] (new edn., 3 vols: London, 1837), vol. III. 1770–1797, p. 306.</note>
                    &amp; the natural effect of an ill digested plan more calculated to overthrow the ministry than anything else. surely we are a sold people: 
                    but everything must a rise that is evil if our american army perhaps pleased with the country join with the loyalists
                    &amp; <hi rend="underline">make a peace</hi> of their own.</p>
                <p>The only use of <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl1010">Gibraltar</placeName> is to get better terms. <note type="editorial">The siege of Gibraltar was lifted in February 1783 and the set of treatises to end the American Revolutionary War, known as the Peace of Paris, 3 September 1783, left Gibraltar with the British.</note>
                    if I was in the house I would risque the madness of the people by moving the giving of it up. I worship the loyal <persName ref="pe0473">Elliot</persName>
                <lb/>Faithful found
                    <lb/>among the faithless. <note type="editorial">Words describing the Seraph Abdiel ('faithful found, / Among the faithless') in John Milton, Paradise Lost, Book 5, lines 896–7.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Your rebuke to <persName ref="pe0014">Moses</persName> is not amiss. He shall for the future only do things I mention in print. 
                    Pray send me <persName ref="pe0329">Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Goslings</persName> note to the amount of the Bill, 
                    &amp; I will pay <persName ref="pe0014">moses</persName>
                </p>
                <closer>I am Dear Sir
                    <lb/>most faithfully <choice>
                        <abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                        </abbr>
                        <expan>yours</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">
                            <choice>
                                <abbr>Tho.</abbr>
                                <expan>Thomas</expan>
                            </choice> Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <dateline> <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0001">Downing</placeName> <choice>
                            <abbr>oct<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            </abbr>
                            <expan>october</expan>
                        </choice> 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1782.</dateline>
                </closer>
                
